azed at how much easier it was.<br>
<br>
I would say that SK would be a safer, easier place to learn (assuming its not camped all to hell).  Another option that is not mentioned (and I havent tried) is dervishes outside ToFS.  They are lower-lvl than wolves (less resists) and not as fast as cougars.  Dont know their hitpoints, tho (pretty easy to see if you have the mana, though - kite a single using CoF - if you can finish it with 20m to spare, you can quad safely).  Some people also start out doing succulents in OT (helps to have a litte VS faction).<br>
<br>
DEFINATELY get the SoTF - it shouldnt be too hard to get at your level - might need a tank and a healer for the goblin hearts (SolA can take a while).  It is one of the best overall wizzy items in the game IMO - both in groups and for soloing.  Your nukes hit for noticeably more and you dont get hit/waste mana pulling your quads.  Great little toy.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
